(2006)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1436,882,1428]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,360,1082,1108]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Distribution:</emphasis>
Known from the Mexican states of 
<collectingRegion box="[786,924,1082,1108]" country="Mexico" name="Tamaulipas" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Tamaulipas</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[937,1057,1082,1108]" country="Mexico" name="Queretaro de Arteaga" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Queretaro</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[1119,1216,1082,1108]" country="Mexico" name="Hidalgo" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Hidalgo</collectingRegion>
, where the species occurs at elevations between 700–1,400 meters in the Sierra Madre 
<collectingRegion box="[945,1045,1122,1148]" country="Democratic Republic of the Congo" name="Orientale" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Oriental</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
